  "id": "implement-with-discernment",
  "name": "implement-with-discernment",
  "type": "basic",
  "description": "Applies deliberate judgment before writing code: evaluating whether to implement at all, scoping to the minimum needed, deferring or rejecting features that add complexity without proportionate value, and stopping when the task is done.",
